HersheyCodes - Hershey Fonts for Codea

-- The Hershey Fonts were originally created by Dr.
-- A. V. Hershey while working at the
-- U. S. National Bureau of Standards.

-- Useful Links:
-- http://emergent.unpythonic.net/software/hershey
-- http://paulbourke.net/dataformats/hershey/

-- Re-encoding of font information and other shenanigans
-- by Tom Bortels bortels@gmail.com November 2011
-- all rights reversed (Hail Eris!)

-- "If I have seen a little further it is by standing
-- on the shoulders of Giants."
-- Isaac Newton

Usage:

-- Hello World
function setup()
   f = HersheyRoman()
end
function draw()
   f:drawstring("Hello World", 100, WIDTH/2)
end

-- Hello World (object-oriented)
function setup()
   f = HersheyRoman()
   f:addlabel("Hello World")
end
function draw()
   f:draw()
end

More complex:

  shoe = f:addlabel("Galoshes!", x, y, size, rot, color)
  -- where x, y are x,y location of lower left
  --       size is the scale multiplier (2 is twice as big)
  --       rot is the rotation in degrees
  --       color is a table { R G B Alpha } (ie. like stroke() )
  fade=255

  -- later, in draw():
  shoe.rot = shoe.rot + 1
  shoe.size = math.sin(ElapsedTime)
  fade = fade - 1
  shoe.color = { 255, 255, 255, fade } -- Poof!  

see main.lua for more (working!) examples. 

Note that main.lua is a demo - you need only add HersheyRoman.lua to your project and go. 
